05:05.555 --> 05:07.264
What is it?

05:12.020 --> 05:15.564
- What do they want?
- I don't know.

05:16.524 --> 05:18.692
Just pass me.

05:19.110 --> 05:20.277
Pass me.

05:25.700 --> 05:28.744
- Is it a cop?
- I can't see.

05:30.455 --> 05:32.649
What the fuck
are these jokers playing at?

05:32.749 --> 05:34.916
Oh, they ain't playing.
You better believe.

05:45.470 --> 05:49.014
- What are we gonna do?
- I don't know.

05:54.312 --> 05:55.937
Okay. Hold on, you guys.

06:07.533 --> 06:08.950
There's a truck, too.

06:26.636 --> 06:28.136
Shit, it is a cop.

06:30.973 --> 06:32.140
You better stop.

06:33.142 --> 06:37.437
Okay, sit tight, you guys.
Don't say anything. Let me talk.

06:38.106 --> 06:40.399
All right. We'll be all right.

06:40.608 --> 06:42.317
Just relax.

07:18.855 --> 07:21.773
Y'all think you can drive
any speed you want around here?

07:21.983 --> 07:24.010
You had us scared to death, man.

07:24.110 --> 07:27.112
Don't call me "man," Jew-boy.

07:27.321 --> 07:28.613
No, sir. What should I call you?

07:28.823 --> 07:31.741
You don't call me nothing,
nigger-loving Jew-boy. You just listen.

07:34.203 --> 07:36.121
Yes, sir.

07:37.748 --> 07:40.876
Hell, you even starting to smell
like a nigger, Jew-boy.

07:42.211 --> 07:44.004
Take it easy. We'll be all right.

07:44.213 --> 07:45.881
Sure you will, nigger-lover.

07:46.090 --> 07:50.302
He's seen your face. That ain't good.
You don't want him seeing your face.

07:50.511 --> 07:53.581
Oh, it don't make no difference no more.

07:57.477 --> 08:00.088
Oh, shit! We into it now, boys!

08:02.398 --> 08:03.716
You only left me a nigger,

08:03.816 --> 08:05.259
but at least I shot me a nigger.

08:08.196 --> 08:09.613
Yes, indeed.

08:33.929 --> 08:36.932
Now listen, you communists
and niggers and Jews

08:37.099 --> 08:39.893
Tell all your buddies
To spread the news

08:40.102 --> 08:43.270
Your day of judgment
Will soon be nigh

08:43.481 --> 08:46.942
As the Lord in his wisdom
Looks down from on high

08:47.109 --> 08:50.070
Will his battle be lost
By mixing the races?

08:50.279 --> 08:54.199
We want beautiful babies
Not ones with brown faces

08:54.408 --> 08:57.118
Never, never
Never I say

08:57.286 --> 08:59.037
For the Ku Klux Klan
Is here to stay

08:59.247 --> 09:01.373
Never, never
Never I say

09:01.582 --> 09:04.501
'Cause the Ku Klux Klan
Is here to stay

09:04.710 --> 09:07.504
These Ku Kluxers are better
with lynchings than they are with lyrics.

09:08.381 --> 09:13.202
Just read the file, Mr. Anderson.
I can do without the cabaret.

09:13.302 --> 09:14.745
You don't like me much, do you, boss?

09:14.845 --> 09:16.263
Sure I like you.

09:16.806 --> 09:18.348
I just don't share your sense of humor.

09:20.226 --> 09:22.477
Sometimes that's all you got left.

09:22.728 --> 09:23.838
How long you been in the bureau?

09:23.938 --> 09:25.021
Three years.

09:25.565 --> 09:27.467
Right out of college, huh?

09:27.567 --> 09:29.901
No. From the Justice Department.

09:30.444 --> 09:33.321
Kennedy boy. Now I see.

09:33.823 --> 09:37.158
No, I don't think you do see.

09:37.368 --> 09:39.828
Let's get this thing straight.

09:39.996 --> 09:43.373
I haven't had a pimple in years.
I shave every morning.

09:43.583 --> 09:45.234
I even go to the bathroom by myself.

09:45.334 --> 09:48.003
So you can quit this "boss" stuff.

09:48.921 --> 09:51.756
They put me in charge
because I've been through this before.

09:51.966 --> 09:54.342
- Birmingham? Montgomery?
- Oxford.

09:54.677 --> 09:57.679
I was with Meredith at Ole Miss.

09:57.888 --> 10:00.810
Got hit in the head with a brick,
so they gave you a promotion, right?

10:01.110 --> 10:03.318
No. Shot in the shoulder.

10:04.937 --> 10:06.688
Well, at least you lived.
That's important.

10:06.897 --> 10:10.525
No, Meredith lived.
That's what's important.

10:17.783 --> 10:19.951
What's got four eyes and can't see?

10:21.829 --> 10:24.414
- What?
- Mississippi.

10:26.667 --> 10:28.945
Never, never
Never I say

10:29.045 --> 10:32.355
'Cause the Ku Klux Klan
Is here to...

11:05.247 --> 11:07.582
Big building for a small town.

11:11.796 --> 11:13.296
Howdy.

11:46.247 --> 11:47.455
Good morning.

11:48.082 --> 11:52.210
My name's Alan Ward. I'm with the FBI.

11:53.170 --> 11:56.381
Federal Bureau of Integration?

11:59.301 --> 12:01.469
In that get-up, you ain't exactly
undercover, are you, now?

12:01.887 --> 12:04.081
We're here to see Sheriff Stuckey.

12:04.181 --> 12:06.474
Sheriff's right busy now.

12:08.477 --> 12:11.396
You'll have to wait
or come back some other time.

12:13.858 --> 12:15.483
We'll wait.

12:28.038 --> 12:30.915
Listen to me,
you backwoods shit-ass, you.

12:31.125 --> 12:33.752
You got about two seconds
to get the sheriff out here,

12:33.961 --> 12:36.504
or I'm gonna kick
the goddamned door in, okay?

12:40.217 --> 12:43.371
Well, hell, looks like
we got some company.

12:43.471 --> 12:45.706
Some Hoover boys come down to visit.

12:45.806 --> 12:47.724
- How you doing?
- Good.

12:48.350 --> 12:49.543
I'm Sheriff Stuckey.

12:49.643 --> 12:50.769
Rupert Anderson.

12:51.437 --> 12:53.756
- Rupert? We been expecting you.
- Uh-huh.

12:53.856 --> 12:56.232
I assume you met my deputy, Mr. Pell?

12:56.901 --> 12:58.109
Sure did.

12:58.569 --> 13:01.237
You down here to help us solve
our nigger problems?

13:01.614 --> 13:04.016
No. It's just a missing-person case.

13:04.116 --> 13:05.909
Hmm. Well, come on.

13:07.077 --> 13:09.689
Say, you gonna want your boy in on this?

13:09.789 --> 13:11.998
Sheriff, I'm Special Agent Ward.

13:12.208 --> 13:14.542
I'm in charge of this case.

13:15.044 --> 13:18.338
We think it might be a little more serious
than missing persons.

13:19.340 --> 13:20.882
I don't think so, boy.

13:21.050 --> 13:24.385
In fact, you know what I think it is,
it's a publicity stunt

13:24.595 --> 13:27.680
cooked up by that
Martin Luther King fella.

13:27.890 --> 13:29.766
Come on.

13:41.987 --> 13:46.032
At around 3:00 p.m., Deputy Pell says
he arrested the three boys for speeding.

13:46.242 --> 13:49.828
He held them in jail until 10:00 p.m.,
and then released them.

13:50.037 --> 13:51.579
They drove off.

13:51.747 --> 13:54.233
He says he followed them
as far as the county line

13:54.333 --> 13:57.085
and never saw them again.

13:58.337 --> 14:00.129
Why didn't they make a phone call?

14:00.756 --> 14:02.074
Why should they?

14:02.174 --> 14:04.801
Mr. Anderson, these boys
were trained activists.

14:05.010 --> 14:06.996
They're taught to check in every hour,

14:07.096 --> 14:09.222
and if they're arrested, the moment
they're released from custody.

14:09.431 --> 14:13.476
The hotel's two minutes from the jail.
They could have phoned from the lobby.

14:13.686 --> 14:15.103
It just doesn't follow.

14:15.271 --> 14:16.672
Maybe they went for a beer.

14:16.772 --> 14:18.064
Not these boys.

14:18.274 --> 14:21.734
The civil rights office in Rossville started
making calls as soon as they didn't check in.

14:22.486 --> 14:26.656
The sheriff's office here said
they had no idea where the boys were.

14:27.575 --> 14:28.658
First lie.

14:31.871 --> 14:34.747
By who? The sheriff's office
or the civil rights office?

14:35.040 --> 14:37.041
Who would you believe?

14:37.293 --> 14:39.236
Mr. Ward, I don't know
if you knew it or not,

14:39.336 --> 14:41.504
but I was a sheriff in a little
Mississippi town just like this.

14:41.714 --> 14:43.073
Yes, I'm aware of that, Mr. Anderson.

14:43.173 --> 14:45.034
Well, lying just don't come into it.

14:45.134 --> 14:46.827
We were right on the border,
10 miles from Memphis,

14:46.927 --> 14:48.996
and a million miles
from the rest of the world.

14:49.096 --> 14:52.098
Now, if a sheriff in a little town like this
says that's what happened,

14:52.308 --> 14:54.392
then that's what happened.

14:54.602 --> 14:55.935
Let's go eat.

15:11.160 --> 15:13.896
We're full up right now, honey.
Y'all wanna wait a while?

15:13.996 --> 15:15.246
Is the wait worth it?

15:15.456 --> 15:18.875
We're not full for nothing, sugar.
Y'all want to look at a menu while you wait?

15:19.084 --> 15:20.668
- Sure.
- Thank you.

15:22.463 --> 15:23.963
Well, what y'all gonna do,
wait or leave?

15:25.132 --> 15:28.009
We're gonna wait because
we want to be near you.

15:28.218 --> 15:30.511
There's some empty seats down there.

15:30.721 --> 15:32.055
Uh, Mr. Ward.

15:33.015 --> 15:36.017
That's the colored down there.
Don't even think about it.

15:36.226 --> 15:38.337
There's some people over here
getting ready to leave right now.

15:38.437 --> 15:40.688
Aren't you hungry, Mr. Anderson?

15:50.115 --> 15:52.867
Good afternoon. Looks good.

16:03.879 --> 16:06.547
Do you mind if I ask you
a few questions?

16:06.757 --> 16:08.925
I'm looking for some information.

16:11.929 --> 16:13.747
I ain't got nothing to say to you, sir.

16:13.847 --> 16:15.390
Just a few questions.

16:20.270 --> 16:23.439
I ain't got nothing to say to you, sir.

16:41.709 --> 16:43.819
Three civil rights boys came here

16:43.919 --> 16:47.046
to propose setting up a voter
registration clinic.

16:47.339 --> 16:50.633
Before the locals got a chance to say yes,
the Klan burned them down.

16:50.843 --> 16:53.011
Give a man a vote,
but don't let him use it.

16:53.220 --> 16:55.080
That's the way it works.

16:55.180 --> 16:57.056
What'd their office in Rossville
have to say?

16:57.266 --> 17:01.894
They confirmed that the boys came back
here to apologize to the congregation.

17:02.604 --> 17:04.548
Sorry you folks didn't get to vote.

17:04.647 --> 17:07.900
I suppose most of you never knew
you even had one.

17:08.277 --> 17:10.903
Now you got no place to go on Sunday.

17:12.948 --> 17:16.951
Apparently, after they came back here,
they talked to some locals down the road.

17:17.161 --> 17:18.520
I think that's where we should start.

17:18.619 --> 17:22.398
Well, you can talk to them,
but they won't talk to you.

17:22.499 --> 17:25.778
These people have to live here
long after we're packed up and gone.

17:25.877 --> 17:27.795
They'd rather bite
their tongue off than talk to us.

17:28.547 --> 17:30.381
Bureau procedure, Mr. Anderson.

17:38.265 --> 17:42.060
The church caught fire
and you ran home, is that correct?

17:42.686 --> 17:44.020
Yes, sir.

17:44.229 --> 17:46.966
Then the four white men stopped you?

17:47.066 --> 17:48.399
Yes, sir.

17:48.650 --> 17:51.152
These four white men
attacked your husband?

17:52.112 --> 17:53.863
Yes, sir.

17:54.573 --> 17:56.991
But you can't identify them?

17:58.827 --> 18:00.453
No, sir.

18:01.246 --> 18:03.857
Did you report this to the police?

18:03.957 --> 18:05.917
No, sir.

18:06.585 --> 18:08.988
But you told
the civil rights boys what happened?

18:09.088 --> 18:10.671
Yes, sir.

18:12.007 --> 18:16.135
Ma'am, did they tell you where they
were going after that?

18:19.348 --> 18:20.556
No, sir.

18:20.766 --> 18:22.584
Nothing?

18:22.684 --> 18:24.685
No, sir.

18:26.605 --> 18:28.940
All right. Thank you, ma'am.

18:29.149 --> 18:31.025
You're welcome.

18:43.789 --> 18:45.331
Come on, boy.

18:45.541 --> 18:46.833
Open up.

18:48.794 --> 18:49.945
Your brother Hollis here?

18:50.045 --> 18:51.129
Yes, sir.

18:51.338 --> 18:53.714
Well, wake his ass up.
We want to see him.

18:53.882 --> 18:55.675
- Why?
- Just wake him up, boy.

18:55.884 --> 18:56.952
Why? What's the matter?

18:57.052 --> 18:58.386
There you are!

19:01.181 --> 19:02.765
Come here, boy!

19:03.225 --> 19:04.334
Hollis!

19:06.061 --> 19:08.396
Get your ass back here,
you fucking nigger!

19:08.605 --> 19:11.274
Hollis! Hollis!

19:17.823 --> 19:19.115
Shit!

19:26.623 --> 19:29.417
We better not catch you
talking to the FBI.

19:29.585 --> 19:31.669
You'll be dead, boy.

19:50.230 --> 19:52.356
You admire these kids, don't you?

19:53.567 --> 19:54.775
Don't you?

19:56.195 --> 19:58.529
I think they're being used.

19:59.323 --> 20:02.783
I think they're sent down here in their
Volkswagens and their sneakers,

20:02.951 --> 20:04.744
just to get their heads cracked open.

20:04.953 --> 20:08.331
Did it ever occur to you that maybe
they believed in what they were doing?

20:08.540 --> 20:10.609
Did it ever occur to them
they were gonna end up dead?

20:10.709 --> 20:12.001
Maybe.

20:13.128 --> 20:15.796
In Washington they sure as hell knew,
didn't they?

20:16.548 --> 20:18.174
Some things are worth dying for.

20:21.136 --> 20:24.305
Down here they see
things a little differently.

20:26.058 --> 20:28.726
People down here
feel some things are worth killing for.

20:32.856 --> 20:36.442
Where does it come from,
all this hatred?

20:39.404 --> 20:41.822
You know, when I was a little boy,

20:42.032 --> 20:45.284
an old Negro farmer lived
down the road, name of Monroe.

20:46.411 --> 20:47.662
And he was, uh...

20:48.830 --> 20:52.583
I guess he was luckier
than my daddy was.

20:56.546 --> 20:58.673
He bought himself a mule.

21:00.217 --> 21:03.177
That was a big deal around that town.

21:03.637 --> 21:06.138
My daddy hated that mule.

21:06.348 --> 21:08.458
His friends always kidded him about

21:08.558 --> 21:11.686
Monroe plowing with his new mule.

21:11.853 --> 21:16.941
And Monroe was gonna rent another
field now that he had a mule.

21:18.527 --> 21:21.696
One morning that mule
just showed up dead.

21:23.782 --> 21:26.158
They poisoned the water.

21:27.286 --> 21:30.413
After that, the mule
wasn't mentioned to my daddy.

21:30.622 --> 21:32.707
Just never came up.

21:35.919 --> 21:40.548
Once, driving along, we passed
Monroe's place and it was empty.

21:40.757 --> 21:44.051
He packed and left.
Gone up north or something.

21:46.513 --> 21:50.391
I looked over at my daddy's face

21:51.476 --> 21:54.103
and I knew he'd done it.

21:54.313 --> 21:58.566
He saw that I knew. He was ashamed.

21:59.401 --> 22:02.028
I guess he was ashamed.

22:04.072 --> 22:05.906
He looked at me and he said,

22:06.742 --> 22:09.577
"If you ain't better than a nigger,
who are you better than?"

22:13.290 --> 22:14.816
You think that's an excuse?

22:14.916 --> 22:18.669
No. It's just a story about my daddy.

22:23.717 --> 22:25.911
Where's that leave you?

22:26.011 --> 22:28.763
With an old man so full of hate

22:28.972 --> 22:33.476
that he didn't know being poor
was what was killing him.

22:41.777 --> 22:43.944
Get the light! Get the light!

22:45.947 --> 22:47.448
You all right?

22:58.251 --> 23:00.294
I guess they know we're here.

23:36.790 --> 23:39.250
Now you know what you're getting into.

23:39.459 --> 23:42.002
I'll call Washington.
I need more agents.

23:42.629 --> 23:46.006
Make any difference if I say
it's the wrong thing to do?

23:46.216 --> 23:47.675
No.

24:35.474 --> 24:38.350
The whole place for $75 a month.

24:38.560 --> 24:41.645
It's private. It's central.
It's perfect.

24:41.855 --> 24:45.024
There's room for 100 more agents.
200, maybe.

24:45.400 --> 24:47.234
More on the balcony.

24:47.402 --> 24:50.138
We're trying to find
the boys, Mr. Anderson.

24:50.238 --> 24:52.281
I'll take all the help I can get.

24:54.534 --> 24:55.534
When's the show start?

25:50.799 --> 25:52.451
Who's the big shot?

25:52.551 --> 25:54.051
That's the Klan.

25:55.178 --> 25:58.681
No pointy hats,
but plenty of pointy heads.

25:59.307 --> 26:02.226
Let me run a check on the plates.

26:32.591 --> 26:35.009
Good afternoon, gentlemen.

26:35.176 --> 26:36.468
Anderson.

26:36.678 --> 26:38.429
Say hello to our mayor, Mr. Tilman.

26:38.805 --> 26:40.457
How do you do, Anderson?

26:40.557 --> 26:42.349
Mr. Mayor, Mr. Barber.

26:43.768 --> 26:45.978
This looks like the place to be.

26:46.563 --> 26:48.272
Even for me.

26:49.566 --> 26:52.943
Nothing like a barber shop
for jawing your socks off.

26:53.737 --> 26:55.764
Where you from, Anderson?

26:55.864 --> 26:57.406
Thornton, Mississippi, sir.

26:57.699 --> 26:59.325
Just a spit from Tennessee.

26:59.534 --> 27:03.037
Then you must know
how we all feel down here.

27:03.204 --> 27:06.874
We don't take to outsiders
telling us how to live.

27:07.083 --> 27:11.170
Our nigras were happy,
till those beatnik college kids

27:11.379 --> 27:15.716
came here stirring things up.
Before that, nobody complained.

27:17.135 --> 27:18.677
Nobody dared.

27:20.388 --> 27:23.349
We got a peaceful community, Anderson.

27:23.558 --> 27:28.395
They're like other folks, I reckon.
You push them too far...

27:28.605 --> 27:33.317
The way I figure it, it's like
three sticks of old dynamite.

27:33.526 --> 27:38.530
You shake it up, and we'll be
scraping bodies off the street.

27:39.282 --> 27:43.619
I'm here to investigate the missing
three kids, ask questions.

27:43.828 --> 27:48.957
If this all boiled down to gravy,
there's not enough for a chicken-fried steak.

27:49.167 --> 27:53.629
Them kids you're looking for?
I'll bet you a shiny new dime

27:53.838 --> 27:56.491
they're sitting in Chicago

27:56.591 --> 27:59.160
drinking a cold beer
and having a big laugh

27:59.260 --> 28:01.178
about all the commotion.

28:01.471 --> 28:02.888
Sure hope so.

28:03.765 --> 28:05.724
You tell your bosses

28:05.934 --> 28:09.269
people got the wrong idea
about the South.

28:09.437 --> 28:11.605
You know what I'm talking about.

28:11.815 --> 28:15.317
Everybody running around
ragged, backwards, illiterate,

28:15.527 --> 28:19.279
eating sow-belly and corn pone
three times a day.

28:19.447 --> 28:23.450
Simple fact is, Anderson,
we got two cultures down here.

28:23.618 --> 28:27.204
White culture, and the colored culture.

28:27.414 --> 28:29.566
That's the way it always has been.

28:29.666 --> 28:31.792
That's the way it always will be.

28:32.001 --> 28:34.070
Rest of America don't see that.

28:34.170 --> 28:36.463
America don't mean jack shit.

28:36.673 --> 28:38.882
You in Mississippi now.

28:39.551 --> 28:41.228
Oh, that's for sure.

28:44.139 --> 28:45.707
What's the score?

28:45.807 --> 28:47.641
St. Louis on top, five to nothing.

28:47.809 --> 28:49.044
What inning is it?

28:49.144 --> 28:50.394
Bottom of the seventh.

28:50.603 --> 28:52.339
You like baseball, Anderson?

28:52.439 --> 28:54.106
Yeah, I do. You know,

28:55.775 --> 29:00.821
it's the only time a black man
can wave a stick at a white man

29:01.448 --> 29:03.365
and not start a riot.

29:19.507 --> 29:20.716
Sir?

29:21.551 --> 29:25.012
We checked on the plate, sir.
Clayton Townley.

29:25.221 --> 29:29.266
Grand Wizard of the White
Knights of the Ku Klux Klan.

29:29.476 --> 29:32.227
That's him.
And we have a lead on the car.

29:32.437 --> 29:34.605
A Choctaw thinks he knows where it is.

29:34.814 --> 29:36.049
I'm waiting for a call.

29:36.149 --> 29:37.357
Good.

29:53.374 --> 29:55.860
You have your appointment
for next Tuesday, right?

29:55.960 --> 29:58.420
See you then. Bye-bye.

30:21.820 --> 30:23.737
You gonna go to...

30:25.031 --> 30:26.824
Afternoon, ladies.

30:27.867 --> 30:29.409
Can I help you?

30:29.619 --> 30:34.331
Well, yes, you can.
I tell you, I hate the way I look.

30:34.541 --> 30:39.711
What do you think? A permanent wave,
maybe? Or a bleach job?

30:39.921 --> 30:43.048
That looks good.
You have that done here?

30:43.258 --> 30:44.492
Jackson.

30:44.592 --> 30:45.801
A wig's your only hope.

30:46.010 --> 30:48.538
You won't be able to do much
with that cue ball.

30:49.848 --> 30:50.973
Thank you.

30:51.182 --> 30:55.227
If you wanna ask questions,
here's where you'll hear it all.

30:55.436 --> 30:58.230
Well, matter of fact, I do.

30:58.439 --> 31:01.650
Who's that gentleman that just drove in?

31:01.860 --> 31:03.636
I know that isn't President Johnson.

31:03.736 --> 31:06.196
Clayton Townley.

31:06.406 --> 31:08.266
Are you one of them FBI gentlemen?

31:08.366 --> 31:10.158
Yes, ma'am, I am.

31:10.368 --> 31:13.521
I think it's a shame
those two kids are dead,

31:13.621 --> 31:15.581
but I hope you find them.

31:15.790 --> 31:19.835
Actually, it's three kids missing.
A colored kid also.

31:20.044 --> 31:24.798
You honestly think you'd be here
if it weren't for the white boys?

31:24.966 --> 31:26.758
- Maybe not, Miss...
- Mrs.

31:27.135 --> 31:30.262
Pell. Her old man's
Ray Stuckey's deputy.

31:33.558 --> 31:35.460
But I'm single.

31:38.146 --> 31:39.980
Look out! Here they come!

31:49.991 --> 31:51.116
Hollis?

31:54.996 --> 31:57.039
Get back. Move out of the way.

32:01.336 --> 32:03.545
It's a local problem.

32:03.755 --> 32:07.007
We'll handle it!
We don't need your damn help!

32:09.427 --> 32:14.681
It ain't right having blood on Main Street.
How'd that look on TV?

32:14.849 --> 32:16.266
- Okay, easy.
- Get up.

32:16.476 --> 32:18.253
I got him.

32:18.353 --> 32:20.103
Get out of the way, now.

32:22.690 --> 32:24.008
He's from the diner.

32:24.108 --> 32:27.861
Think before you talk
to colored kids with an audience.

32:28.029 --> 32:31.073
They're sending a message from Tupelo.

32:31.282 --> 32:34.743
I know it, yes.
Clayton Townley, chief pointy head.

32:34.953 --> 32:37.496
That's right. How did you know?

32:37.705 --> 32:39.816
Bureau procedure. Try it sometime.

32:39.916 --> 32:41.541
We did!

32:41.751 --> 32:44.586
We found the car the kids were driving.

33:24.419 --> 33:25.836
Good morning.

33:34.971 --> 33:36.346
Good morning.

34:58.096 --> 35:02.057
Two beer cans, a Coca Cola bottle,
green plastic bottle,

35:02.266 --> 35:05.560
badly burned wristwatch
stopped at 12:45, set of keys.

35:05.686 --> 35:07.213
No bodies.

35:07.313 --> 35:08.772
I want the entire area searched.

35:08.940 --> 35:10.091
Every inch.

35:10.191 --> 35:11.358
Yes, sir.

35:11.526 --> 35:12.719
It's a big swamp.

35:12.819 --> 35:14.694
Every inch, Mr. Bird.

35:18.282 --> 35:20.951
I guess they never left Mississippi.

35:22.411 --> 35:25.539
Yeah, they're dead. They're dead.

35:25.873 --> 35:27.275
Mr. Bird?

35:27.375 --> 35:28.959
Yes, sir?

35:29.460 --> 35:31.670
There's a telephone at the truck stop.

35:31.879 --> 35:36.883
Get to it, get on it and get me
100 more men here by morning.

35:37.051 --> 35:38.927
- 100?
- 100.

35:39.137 --> 35:40.705
Bureau people?

35:40.805 --> 35:42.347
It could be the goddamn army!

35:42.557 --> 35:44.500
I want this entire swamp searched.

35:44.600 --> 35:45.809
Yes, sir.

35:48.896 --> 35:52.399
Don't do it, Mr. Ward.
You'll just start a war.

35:53.067 --> 35:56.153
It was a war long before we got here.

36:46.287 --> 36:47.271
You too!

36:47.371 --> 36:48.371
Wake up! Come on!

36:53.794 --> 36:57.380
Get the fuck out of here, nigger! Go on!

37:36.837 --> 37:38.171
Sir?

37:39.674 --> 37:44.427
The sheriff's alibi is solid.
He was playing poker with relatives.

37:44.637 --> 37:45.746
The whole time?

37:45.846 --> 37:49.683
No, for three hours. He lost $11.38.

37:50.309 --> 37:51.919
Another thing, sir.

37:52.019 --> 37:54.896
We're having trouble with
the motel manager.

37:55.106 --> 37:56.215
What trouble?

37:56.315 --> 37:57.357
He wants us out.

37:57.566 --> 37:59.427
He says we're bad for business.

37:59.527 --> 38:01.319
Buy it.

38:01.696 --> 38:03.196
Sorry, sir?

38:03.614 --> 38:05.156
Buy it!

38:05.408 --> 38:07.117
The motel.

38:07.368 --> 38:08.853
How high can I go?

38:08.953 --> 38:10.745
Whatever it takes.

38:33.894 --> 38:35.963
Today in Jessup County,

38:36.063 --> 38:38.815
amidst the violence
erupting here this week,

38:39.025 --> 38:41.969
the nation's fixed on the search

38:42.069 --> 38:44.070
for the missing civil rights workers.

38:44.280 --> 38:45.806
I think it's a hoax.

38:45.906 --> 38:49.409
But if they are in that swamp,
then they asked for it.

38:49.618 --> 38:53.246
Naval reserves are in
to join scores of FBI agents

38:53.456 --> 38:55.457
in their search for the men.

38:55.666 --> 39:00.211
They planned the whole thing.
They're in New York laughing at us.

39:00.421 --> 39:01.489
You think it's a hoax?

39:01.589 --> 39:05.425
Yeah. They ain't gonna find nothing.

39:05.593 --> 39:10.096
Civil rights leaders are optimistic
as to the men's whereabouts,

39:10.264 --> 39:14.601
but privately, there is concern
they will ever be found alive.

39:14.769 --> 39:17.354
They looked for trouble and found it.

39:17.563 --> 39:21.941
This is Marek Barlbobi, Network News.
Jessup County, Mississippi.

39:22.151 --> 39:24.486
Sheriff Stuckey?

39:24.945 --> 39:28.615
They ought to be looking up in Canada
for them boys

39:28.783 --> 39:31.326
instead of our swamps here.

39:31.535 --> 39:37.123
Also, I think it's a publicity stunt
dreamed up by these NAACP people.

39:37.333 --> 39:38.526
NAACP?

39:38.626 --> 39:39.918
Yeah, NAACP.

39:40.252 --> 39:45.173
It stands for niggers, alligators, apes,
coons and possums.

39:45.383 --> 39:48.218
Tell you what you got.
You got your NAACP,

39:48.327 --> 39:51.846
you got your SNCC, your COFO...

39:52.056 --> 39:54.015
You know what that mess is?

39:54.225 --> 39:57.560
B-U-L-L-S-H-l-T. You got it?

39:57.770 --> 40:00.522
Sheriff, will this be a federal case?

40:02.274 --> 40:04.927
There'll be a time
when we don't gotta say,

40:05.027 --> 40:07.529
"Good morning, sir, Mr. Sheriff."

40:08.114 --> 40:12.325
There'll be a time when we won't
have to say, "Mr. Stuckey."

40:12.493 --> 40:16.913
There'll be a time when we just say
"Stuckey" or "Sheriff."

40:17.123 --> 40:21.418
There'll be a time when the sheriff
won't even be a white man.

40:33.013 --> 40:34.347
Hello.

40:38.144 --> 40:40.854
Could I ask you a few questions?

40:41.063 --> 40:44.899
I don't suppose you know
what kind of flower these are?

40:45.693 --> 40:48.903
I been seeing them all over the place.

40:49.655 --> 40:52.407
I never saw such a darn pretty plant.

40:53.534 --> 40:55.311
They're trumpet pitchers.

40:55.411 --> 40:57.203
Trumpet pitchers.

40:57.705 --> 41:00.373
They're beautiful. They really are.

41:00.541 --> 41:03.960
They don't smell so good,
but they're pretty.

41:08.257 --> 41:10.409
It's nice talking to you.

41:10.509 --> 41:12.552
Sorry about interrupting your meeting,

41:12.761 --> 41:15.122
but nobody will talk to us.

41:15.222 --> 41:17.515
They "zip up," like my mama used to say.

41:17.808 --> 41:22.103
People don't want to talk
for fear it'll get back to the law.

41:22.688 --> 41:24.090
We are the law.

41:24.190 --> 41:25.523
Not around here.

41:26.358 --> 41:29.694
We were sent to find out
what happened to those three boys.

41:31.363 --> 41:32.807
They were here to help you.

41:32.907 --> 41:34.908
It ain't us you should talk to.

41:35.576 --> 41:37.520
Who should we be talking to?

41:37.620 --> 41:39.162
Come on, Aaron.

41:41.081 --> 41:43.500
Start with the sheriff's office.

41:45.711 --> 41:47.154
Why ain't you afraid?

41:47.254 --> 41:48.614
How come you ain't?

41:48.714 --> 41:49.923
Aaron.

41:51.675 --> 41:53.635
Aaron? Come on, son.

42:07.233 --> 42:10.610
Here's the pitch.
Swing and a line-drive base hit.

42:10.819 --> 42:12.612
Another runner's home.

42:16.033 --> 42:19.285
On to the next pitch
by the ruffled Bob Gibson.

42:19.453 --> 42:24.541
Ron Hunt singled to center.
Hickman scored the Mets' second run.

42:24.750 --> 42:27.961
Hunt holds on at first.
Mets now lead 2 to 1.

42:28.128 --> 42:32.090
The next one up will be Joe Christopher
who struck out and popped out to Boyer.

42:33.842 --> 42:37.804
He's 0 for 2, and hitting a mere.252...

42:39.723 --> 42:43.836
Good evening, Mrs. Pell.
I'm Agent Ward. He's Agent Anderson.

42:43.936 --> 42:47.814
We're with the FBI.
Is your husband home?

42:48.816 --> 42:51.343
We'd like to have a word with him.

42:51.443 --> 42:53.903
Y'all come in, then.

43:00.286 --> 43:04.330
The FBI gentlemen
want to ask you some more questions.

43:04.999 --> 43:07.166
Want me to put your dinner in the oven?

43:09.837 --> 43:11.337
Leave us alone?

43:12.381 --> 43:14.465
Mind if I take a seat?

43:18.345 --> 43:21.014
Why you gotta bother me at home?

43:21.223 --> 43:24.418
Well, I wanted to run through,
once again,

43:24.518 --> 43:26.394
your movements on June 21 st.

43:26.604 --> 43:27.645
June which?

43:28.856 --> 43:31.258
June 21 st.

43:31.358 --> 43:34.110
Now, deputy, we both know
what day we're talking about.

43:34.320 --> 43:38.698
Let's be civilized and the sooner
you can get back to your game

43:38.866 --> 43:40.575
and we can return to DC.

43:51.128 --> 43:53.588
Please, don't let me interrupt you.

43:54.340 --> 43:56.283
It's just when you've heard a question

43:56.383 --> 43:59.677
asked a dozen times, it gets boring.

44:00.387 --> 44:02.639
Yeah, I guess so.

44:09.146 --> 44:10.798
You don't eat together?

44:10.898 --> 44:12.482
He works funny hours.

44:15.194 --> 44:16.319
You think that's odd?

44:16.904 --> 44:17.904
No.

44:19.073 --> 44:21.199
I work funny hours myself.

44:22.993 --> 44:26.037
I eat when I'm hungry,
he eats when he can.

44:26.246 --> 44:29.582
- Can I get you something?
- No, thanks.

44:29.792 --> 44:33.002
Nice house.
How long have you lived here?

44:33.212 --> 44:35.046
I was born here.

44:35.255 --> 44:38.841
But my father lost the house
in a poker game a long time ago.

44:40.844 --> 44:43.596
We've been paying rent ever since.

44:46.684 --> 44:48.559
It's a wicked game.

44:52.022 --> 44:53.481
Poker.

44:54.733 --> 44:56.109
Wicked.

44:56.985 --> 44:58.861
Mr. Anderson?

45:01.407 --> 45:04.450
It was nice talking to you.
Guess I gotta go.

45:08.497 --> 45:11.525
Pork chops still any good?
Bring me a beer?

45:11.625 --> 45:12.959
Good night.

45:14.545 --> 45:17.797
Get back to baseball.
You know what they say?

45:18.006 --> 45:20.618
The only game a black man
can wave a stick...

45:20.718 --> 45:22.969
I already heard that one.

45:28.308 --> 45:31.602
Fifty minutes
of his alibi hinges on his wife.

45:31.812 --> 45:33.464
What's she like?

45:33.564 --> 45:34.939
She's a nice lady.

45:35.149 --> 45:38.693
Tell me, how does
a woman like that end up...

45:38.902 --> 45:40.653
With Shithead in there?

45:40.863 --> 45:45.199
You know what small towns are like.
A girl spends high school

45:45.409 --> 45:49.954
looking for a guy to marry,
then her whole life figuring out why.

45:50.164 --> 45:52.790
Something's wrong. He's too confident.

45:53.000 --> 45:55.585
Did you see the wedding photograph?

45:55.794 --> 45:59.406
His three usher pals
hooked their thumbs in their belts

45:59.506 --> 46:01.924
with three fingers pointing down.

46:02.342 --> 46:05.845
So, what is that?
Some sort of Masonic thing?

46:07.014 --> 46:09.015
KKK.

46:13.687 --> 46:16.048
I know you ain't drunk. I won't argue.

46:16.148 --> 46:18.524
I'm not drunk.

46:20.194 --> 46:22.945
I'll take you
where you can sleep it off.

46:23.739 --> 46:25.573
All right. Hold up.

46:27.993 --> 46:30.411
- Who's driving?
- Watch your head.

47:24.842 --> 47:25.842
Hi.

47:26.301 --> 47:29.971
There was a couple things
I need to check with you.

47:30.180 --> 47:32.166
My husband's not here.

47:32.266 --> 47:34.976
Actually, I wanted to talk to you.

47:35.727 --> 47:37.144
Me?

47:37.938 --> 47:41.357
Well, you better come in, then.

47:44.778 --> 47:46.445
Just take a minute.

47:46.655 --> 47:49.782
My boss, he's kind of a pain.
College kid.

47:49.950 --> 47:53.619
He has to dot all the i's,
cross all the t's.

47:53.787 --> 47:55.522
What do you want to ask me about?

47:55.622 --> 47:57.456
It's a time thing.

47:57.666 --> 47:59.526
A few things we're not clear about...

47:59.626 --> 48:02.670
Should I put your flowers in water?

48:02.880 --> 48:04.755
Actually, they're for you.

48:05.465 --> 48:07.910
They're beautiful.

48:08.010 --> 48:09.802
They are pretty, aren't they?

48:10.012 --> 48:12.805
Don't smell nice, but they're pretty.

48:13.557 --> 48:16.335
Would you like anything? Some tea?

48:16.435 --> 48:17.935
Yeah, I would. Thanks.

48:33.452 --> 48:36.579
Oh, don't look at that.
It's a terrible photo.

48:36.788 --> 48:39.498
Oh, I don't know about that.

48:39.833 --> 48:41.360
Is this recent?

48:41.460 --> 48:43.336
No. I wish.

48:43.503 --> 48:46.365
Well, this sure looks recent to me.

48:46.465 --> 48:48.716
We were married 14 years ago.

48:48.926 --> 48:52.995
Are you kidding me?
No, that... Come on!

48:53.347 --> 48:54.540
You take sugar?

48:54.640 --> 48:55.765
Sure do.

48:57.017 --> 48:59.211
I grew up in a town like this.

48:59.311 --> 49:01.520
You were smart enough to leave.

49:01.688 --> 49:03.757
Why didn't you?

49:03.857 --> 49:05.900
"For better or for worse."

49:09.529 --> 49:12.406
How about you? Are you married?

49:12.616 --> 49:13.741
Two.

49:13.951 --> 49:17.286
Well, I was, as I remember.

49:17.496 --> 49:20.414
It didn't last very long.
I was never home.

49:20.624 --> 49:24.377
I guess she got fed up
with phone calls from Miami

49:24.586 --> 49:27.213
and postcards from Des Moines.

49:27.589 --> 49:29.840
There was always a guy around.

49:30.592 --> 49:34.971
Any guy that could spare the time
for a movie or a beer

49:35.180 --> 49:37.264
or a quarter for the jukebox.

49:39.893 --> 49:41.560
She left.

49:45.691 --> 49:47.134
How about you?

49:47.234 --> 49:50.111
Oh, you know the South, Mr. Anderson.

49:50.779 --> 49:54.824
You graduate and marry
the first boy that makes you laugh.

49:55.033 --> 49:57.159
Your husband's quite a guy.

49:59.663 --> 50:03.833
You know, my boss has
this thing about an hour,

50:04.084 --> 50:08.421
50 minutes to be exact,
that your husband says he was with you.

50:12.342 --> 50:14.135
And I guess he was.

50:14.344 --> 50:16.012
Guess he was.

50:19.182 --> 50:21.058
Well, that's a pity.

50:22.602 --> 50:27.273
That means I don't have an excuse
for hanging around here anymore.

50:29.443 --> 50:30.693
Well...

50:32.029 --> 50:33.680
Thank you for the iced tea.

50:33.780 --> 50:35.448
Thank you for the flowers.

50:35.615 --> 50:36.824
Sure.

50:39.453 --> 50:41.620
Do you know what kind they are?

50:42.539 --> 50:45.025
They're called trumpet pitchers.

50:45.125 --> 50:46.333
Oh, that's right.

50:46.543 --> 50:50.463
My daddy called them ladies from hell
because they're car...

50:50.672 --> 50:52.199
Carnivorous.

50:52.299 --> 50:53.716
That's the word?

50:54.468 --> 50:56.828
See, that pretty color's the bait.

50:56.928 --> 50:59.831
Insects home in, and they're dead

50:59.931 --> 51:02.558
even before they got their shoes off.

51:05.645 --> 51:07.881
Should've picked something fitting.

51:07.981 --> 51:09.648
Maybe.

52:24.391 --> 52:27.210
May the peace and the joy
in the Holy Ghost

52:27.310 --> 52:30.354
abide with you for now
and forever. Amen.

52:34.442 --> 52:37.637
He sure did preach
a good sermon today.

53:39.674 --> 53:41.910
You already been told once, nigger!

53:42.010 --> 53:44.303
We don't want to tell you again!

53:44.512 --> 53:48.557
You flap them bootlips off
to any of them federal men,

53:48.767 --> 53:51.628
we'll put you in the ground, boy.

53:51.728 --> 53:54.104
And that's without a pine box!

53:55.523 --> 53:57.483
You understand me?

54:09.955 --> 54:12.498
How are Negroes treated in Mississippi?

54:12.707 --> 54:17.002
They're treated about fair.
About as good as they ought to be.

54:23.009 --> 54:27.554
If you ask me, niggers here have been
treated bad for a long time.

54:37.941 --> 54:41.277
I think Martin Luther King's
one of the leaders.

54:41.486 --> 54:44.280
J. Edgar Hoover said he was a Communist.

54:44.489 --> 54:48.617
They had proof to that effect,
but I don't know for sure.

54:48.827 --> 54:51.370
But that's what they say.

55:05.135 --> 55:07.303
You wanna find that nigger?

55:07.512 --> 55:12.850
They say we've got to eat together
and use the same bathrooms as the niggers.

55:13.059 --> 55:16.228
That's hard for some
Mississippi folks to do.

55:16.396 --> 55:20.316
They're not like us.
They don't take baths. They stink.

55:20.525 --> 55:22.234
They... They're nasty.

55:22.736 --> 55:24.903
They just not like white folks.

55:30.785 --> 55:32.812
What do you think happened to them?

55:32.912 --> 55:34.705
Dead.

55:36.041 --> 55:38.167
Just as dead as they can be.

55:39.085 --> 55:40.961
Feels so good.

55:43.465 --> 55:45.591
Is she asleep? Is she?

55:48.553 --> 55:51.430
I'm sorry I woke you up.

55:53.350 --> 55:54.501
Bye, hon. I'll be a couple hours.

55:54.601 --> 55:55.684
All right.

55:56.561 --> 55:59.271
Well, Mary, is that your Betsy's kid?

55:59.814 --> 56:03.359
Yeah, she's growing up
real quick, isn't she?

56:08.448 --> 56:09.656
Come on.

56:12.660 --> 56:15.245
Tuesday will be just fine on those.

56:20.752 --> 56:22.044
Funny.

56:24.631 --> 56:26.840
Their kids are so cute.

56:33.223 --> 56:35.557
- Here we go.
- That back on me again?

56:35.767 --> 56:39.645
If the Secret Service
couldn't protect the president,

56:39.813 --> 56:43.649
how the hell are we supposed
to protect a few nigras?

56:43.858 --> 56:48.612
It ain't nothing but low-life white trash
drinking too much alcohol.

56:48.822 --> 56:53.450
More like paint thinner,
because this state's as dry as a martini.

56:53.660 --> 56:55.828
We got the drunks to prove it.

56:57.214 --> 57:01.401
Give me a little room here.
Excuse me. Excuse me, Bob.

57:02.961 --> 57:04.946
- Is this okay?
- Your name, please?

57:05.046 --> 57:07.714
Clayton Townley, local businessman.

57:07.966 --> 57:11.969
Are you a spokesman for
the White Knights of the KKK?

57:12.387 --> 57:15.305
I told you. I'm a businessman.

57:15.515 --> 57:19.017
I'm also a Mississippian
and an American.

57:19.185 --> 57:22.354
I'm sick and tired
of the way Mississippians

57:22.522 --> 57:25.983
are having our views distorted
by you media people.

57:26.192 --> 57:28.193
So let's get this straight.

57:28.361 --> 57:32.030
We do not accept Jews
because they reject Christ.

57:32.198 --> 57:37.369
Their control of international banking
cartels are at the root of Communism.

57:37.579 --> 57:41.165
We do not accept papists
who bow to a Roman dictator.

57:41.374 --> 57:45.169
We don't accept Turks,
Mongols, Tartars, Orientals or Negroes.

57:45.378 --> 57:50.817
We're here to protect Anglo-Saxon
democracy and the American way.

57:50.917 --> 57:52.751
Thank you, sir.

57:55.263 --> 57:59.391
Lester, you are living proof
that cousins shouldn't fuck.

58:02.020 --> 58:04.855
There's this colored boy.

58:05.064 --> 58:08.233
He wants to play football
for Bear Bryant.

58:08.401 --> 58:10.929
Bear says, "I'll give you a tryout."

58:11.029 --> 58:12.196
What color was he?

58:12.405 --> 58:15.199
What's he gonna run with? A watermelon?

58:15.909 --> 58:18.327
And he'll keep on running too.

58:18.536 --> 58:21.455
He says, "Get down there
on one goal line."

58:21.664 --> 58:24.458
The other team's on the other goal line.

58:24.667 --> 58:26.319
He throws the boy the ball...

58:32.091 --> 58:33.910
Are you open?

58:34.010 --> 58:35.761
